        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-09-29 16:29:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nWhy are we changing this path again? I would prefer any further change on VES external path be deferred post Guilin branching is done",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "37bdf8d79a9c521e0bf5ad3a03ef83806323f72a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5597,
          "name": "Damian Nowak",
          "display_name": "Damian Nowak",
          "email": "damian.nowak@nokia.com",
          "username": "deen1985"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-09-30 08:07:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: -Code-Review\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n> \n> Why are we changing this path again? I would prefer any further change on VES external path be deferred post Guilin branching is done\n\nVijay,\n\nThe reason why these paths are changed is, that 3GPP has finally completed the SA5 group repo migration to its final shape. As we agreed, we were observing changes there, and as we got a confirmation, that the current structure is a target structure. This is why we have updated the path to something agreed as a final structure.\n\nWell, we can defer to Honolulu, but I think, if we`re before the RC0 of Guilin, and we have a chance to point to the final structure of repo, we shall consider aligning with 3GPP.\n\n(Honestly, the \"old repo\" SA5/trial/data-models/ has been moved to SA5/MnS/ - I am not sure, if the existing link will still work - I tested the new links - they work properly)\n\nDamian",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "fc7fa8472a6addb582cd1fd3066d0557844785d3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 93,
          "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
          "username": "vv770d"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-09-30 15:52:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\n> Patch Set 2: -Code-Review\n> \n> > Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n> > \n> > Why are we changing this path again? I would prefer any further change on VES external path be deferred post Guilin branching is done\n> \n> Vijay,\n> \n> The reason why these paths are changed is, that 3GPP has finally completed the SA5 group repo migration to its final shape. As we agreed, we were observing changes there, and as we got a confirmation, that the current structure is a target structure. This is why we have updated the path to something agreed as a final structure.\n> \n> Well, we can defer to Honolulu, but I think, if we`re before the RC0 of Guilin, and we have a chance to point to the final structure of repo, we shall consider aligning with 3GPP.\n> \n> (Honestly, the \"old repo\" SA5/trial/data-models/ has been moved to SA5/MnS/ - I am not sure, if the existing link will still work - I tested the new links - they work properly)\n> \n> Damian\n\nOkay, thanks for clarification Damain. The old links still, however if these path are final - I'm okay to move forward with this patch for Guilin. \nThis also requires update on VNFREQ (https://docs.onap.org/projects/onap-vnfrqts-requirements/en/latest/Chapter7/Monitoring-And-Management.html#R-408818)\n\nLooping Trevor and Oskar to check as well; can merge if no other concerns noted.",
        "patchset_number": 2
